The paper deals with the interplay between massive MIMO and underlaid D2D networking, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and communication (cs.NI), system and control theory (cs.SY), signal processing (cs.MM), and game theory (cs.GT). The paper discusses the impact of D2D underlay on cellular and D2D spectral efficiency, which requires knowledge of information theory and signal processing. The use of massive MIMO to mitigate interference involves system and control theory. The paper also discusses the trade-off between cellular and D2D performance, which is a topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.GT.
